This paper proposes a stacked deep learning model for sentiment analysis from medical forum data and a probabilistic model for suggesting suitable treatments or procedures for a particular disease or health condition. The paper focuses on the use of social media for healthcare recommendations, which falls under the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), social and information networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and computers and society (cs.CY).
